## API Contract

All routes are prefixed `/api/v1/`. Auth is a Bearer JWT issued at `/auth/callback`.
Webhook auth uses `X-Hub-Signature-256` HMAC validation (not Bearer).

### Endpoints

| Method  | Path                 | Auth                  | Request body / Query params | Success response                          |
| ------- | -------------------- | --------------------- | --------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `POST`  | `/webhooks/github`   | GitHub HMAC signature | Raw webhook payload         | `202 Accepted`                            |
| `GET`   | `/auth/github`       | None                  | —                           | `302` redirect to GitHub OAuth            |
| `GET`   | `/auth/callback`     | None                  | `?code=&state=`             | `200 AuthTokenDTO`                        |
| `GET`   | `/repos`             | Bearer JWT            | —                           | `200 list[RepoDTO]`                       |
| `GET`   | `/repos/{id}/config` | Bearer JWT            | —                           | `200 AgentConfigDTO`                      |
| `PATCH` | `/repos/{id}/config` | Bearer JWT            | `UpdateAgentConfigRequest`  | `200 AgentConfigDTO`                      |
| `GET`   | `/reviews`           | Bearer JWT            | `?repo_id=&page=1&limit=20` | `200 PaginatedResponse[ReviewSummaryDTO]` |
| `GET`   | `/reviews/{id}`      | Bearer JWT            | —                           | `200 ReviewDetailDTO`                     |
| `GET`   | `/jobs/{id}`         | Bearer JWT            | —                           | `200 JobStatusDTO`                        |

### Error Response Shape (consistent across all endpoints)

```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "NOT_FOUND",
    "message": "Review with id 'abc-123' not found.",
    "details": {}
  }
}
```

- `code` — machine-readable string constant (see table below)
- `message` — human-readable description, safe to display in UI
- `details` — optional object with field-level validation errors (VALIDATION_ERROR only)

### Error Codes

| HTTP Status | Error Code         | When used                                                                 |
| ----------- | ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `400`       | `BAD_REQUEST`      | Malformed request body or query params                                    |
| `401`       | `UNAUTHORIZED`     | Missing or invalid Bearer JWT                                             |
| `403`       | `FORBIDDEN`        | Valid JWT but insufficient permission (wrong repo owner)                  |
| `404`       | `NOT_FOUND`        | Resource does not exist                                                   |
| `409`       | `CONFLICT`         | Duplicate resource (e.g. re-review same commit SHA before completion)     |
| `422`       | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | Pydantic validation failed; `details` contains field errors               |
| `429`       | `RATE_LIMITED`     | Gemini API rate limit hit; client should retry after `Retry-After` header |
| `500`       | `INTERNAL_ERROR`   | Unexpected server error; do not expose stack trace                        |
| `502`       | `UPSTREAM_ERROR`   | GitHub API or Gemini API returned an unexpected error                     |

### Validation Error Details Shape

```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
    "message": "Request body validation failed.",
    "details": {
      "fields": [
        {
          "field": "min_severity",
          "message": "must be one of: critical, high, medium, low, info"
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

### Auth Flow

```
1. Frontend redirects user to GET /api/v1/auth/github
2. Backend redirects to https://github.com/login/oauth/authorize?...
3. GitHub redirects back to GET /api/v1/auth/callback?code=...&state=...
4. Backend exchanges code for GitHub token, fetches user profile
5. Backend issues signed JWT (HS256, 7-day expiry) with { sub: user_id, github_id, login }
6. Frontend stores JWT in localStorage; attaches as Authorization: Bearer <token>
7. All /api/v1/* routes (except /webhooks/github and /auth/*) require valid JWT
```

### Webhook Event Routing

| `action` field | What we do                                                              |
| -------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `opened`       | Enqueue review job                                                      |
| `synchronize`  | Enqueue review job (full base→head diff)                                |
| `reopened`     | Enqueue review job                                                      |
| `closed`       | Enqueue embedding cleanup job (delete `code_embeddings` for `head_sha`) |
| anything else  | Acknowledge (202) and discard                                           |

### Webhook Signature Validation

```
1. Receive POST /api/v1/webhooks/github
2. Compute HMAC-SHA256(body_bytes, GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET)
3. Compare with X-Hub-Signature-256 header (constant-time comparison)
4. Reject with 401 if mismatch — never process unsigned webhooks
5. Return 202 immediately after enqueuing; do not await pipeline completion
```

### Rate Limit Handling (Gemini API)

When the Gemini API returns a 429:

- Retry up to 3 times with exponential backoff: 2s, 8s, 32s
- If all retries fail, mark `review_job.status = 'failed'` with `error_message`
- The worker will not retry automatically (already at max attempts)
- Surface the failure in the dashboard job status view
